{{Top|canon=Kitel Phard dynasty}}
The '''Kitel Phard Dynasty''' established an empire across [[Atrisia/Legends|Kitel Phard]], creating a golden age by destroying all opposition to its rule. Even thousands of [[Standard year/Legends|years]] later, the people of the planet looked back on the dynasty with pride.

[[Uueg Tching]] was the 54th Emperor of the dynasty. Other, later, members of the dynasty included [[Oeana Tching]], called the "Invisible Empress," and [[Eoaq the Expansive|Eoaq]] the Expansive. They also were renowned for their Atrisian warriors.

The dynasty had also served some influence within the [[Imperial Military/Legends|military forces]] of the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]]. More specifically, the [[Atrisian corps]] of the [[Imperial Army/Legends|Imperial Army]] had been named after the ancient Atrisian warriors of the Kitel Phard Dynasty.

==Behind the scenes==
This name appears in an e-mail sent to certain purchasers of the [[Star Wars: X-Wing (video game)|''Star Wars: X-Wing'']] CD-ROM, relating to a fake synopsis for a rumored ''Star Wars'' prequel entitled ''The Clone Wars''. The Kitel Phard Dynasty was set to be the major evil organization of the film.<ref name="Blog-pablog|114">{{Blog|pablog|114|A Scam from a Decade Ago}}</ref>

